& [SourceSet] is research evidence
  + [source_001] is Mazur and Rubin, "Controlling Selmer groups in the higher core rank case"
    = url: https://arxiv.org/abs/1312.4052
    = evidence: higher-core-rank Kolyvagin and Stark systems can control the size and structure of Selmer groups under hypotheses
    = boundary: this is an abstract control framework and does not by itself supply a generalized Heegner or Chow-Heegner source factory for arbitrary analytic rank
  + [source_002] is Howard, "The Heegner point Kolyvagin system"
    = url: https://wstein.org/misc/sagedays18_papers/howard-the_heegner_point_kolyvagin_system.pdf
    = evidence: Heegner point Kolyvagin systems give rank/control consequences from Heegner point data in the classical corridor
    = boundary: the source is Heegner-point based and does not close the general higher-rank source-count problem
  + [source_003] is Darmon, "Derived p-adic heights"
    = url: https://www.math.mcgill.ca/darmon/pub/Articles/Research/13.Derived-p-adic/paper.pdf
    = evidence: derived p-adic heights provide higher-order height pairings and derived-regulator measurement
    = boundary: measurement of higher-order Selmer information is not construction of enough independent Mordell-Weil generators
  + [source_004] is Nekovar, "On p-adic height pairings"
    = url: https://webusers.imj-prg.fr/~jan.nekovar/pu/height.pdf
    = evidence: p-adic height pairings are developed broadly for Selmer groups and motivic cycle contexts
    = boundary: height pairings supply measurement infrastructure, not the missing source-count plus upper-control theorem package
  + [source_005] is Sakamoto, "On Selmer complexes, Stark systems and derived p-adic heights"
    = url: https://arxiv.org/html/2603.23978v1
    = evidence: recent work relates Selmer complexes, Stark systems, derived p-adic heights, and a canonical Heegner point Stark system that controls Selmer groups
    = boundary: the result strengthens the abstract/control-measurement interface but remains Heegner-point/Stark-system structured rather than a general BSD rank-parametrized source-transfer package
  + [source_006] is Zhang, "Selmer groups and the indivisibility of Heegner points"
    = url: https://math.mit.edu/~wz2113/math/online/Kconj.pdf
    = evidence: refined Heegner-point divisibility statements support rank-one BSD-style control consequences under suitable hypotheses
    = boundary: the result reinforces special-rank corridors rather than closing arbitrary higher-rank source sufficiency

